The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 23: Inflation rose to 0.26 per cent on the back of higher prices of essential food articles such as vegetables and cereals after falling for two consecutive weeks. Inflation rose 0.08 percentage points during the week ended April 11 from 0.18 per cent a week earlier.                             
	 New Delhi, April 23: NHPC plans to delay its Rs 1,680-crore IPO to tide itself over the current depression in the securities market. The firm planned to seek an extension from Sebi for the approval it had got for the IPO  the biggest in the country in terms of the number of shares on offer.                            
	 Washington, April 23: The World Bank would like New Delhi to take up more responsibilities in mitigating the global economic crisis. It said India under Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and Planning Commission deputy chairman Montek Singh Ahluwalia had a great team.                                                                                                                           
